Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and slice @zucchini{1} crosswise into 1⁄2-inch-thick rounds. Dice @tomato{1} into 1⁄4 inch pieces. Quarter @lemon{1}. Roughly chop @dill{¼%ounce}.

Toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack, until tender and lightly browned, ~{14-16%minutes}.

> If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

While zucchini roasts, in a #small pot{} combine @Israeli couscous{5%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, and 1 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until tender, ~{8-10%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While couscous cooks, open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken, half the @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, juice from half the lemon, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, whisk together @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, and remaining garlic powder. Add water 1 teaspoon at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Serve zucchini, couscous, chicken, tomato salad, garlic sauce, dill, @sliced almonds{½%ounce}, and remaining lemon wedges family style and let everyone to build their own bowls.

> Dash with your favorite hot sauce if you like things spicy!

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.